1
00:01:39,010 --> 00:01:41,559
[Episode 5]

2
00:01:42,559 --> 00:01:45,497
It looks delicious.

3
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:51,559
Qing Ye. This is our Zhazhating specialty.

4
00:01:51,559 --> 00:01:53,559
First-come, first-served.

5
00:01:53,559 --> 00:01:55,397
Here we go.

6
00:01:55,397 --> 00:01:57,520
Come on.

7
00:01:57,520 --> 00:02:00,135
I'll just use my hands then.

8
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:03,839
You look so happy.

9
00:02:03,839 --> 00:02:06,319
It's my first time fighting for food.

10
00:02:06,319 --> 00:02:10,719
My time here has brought me
a lot of brand-new experiences.

11
00:02:10,719 --> 00:02:13,640
Cousin, I won't go easy on you.

12
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:15,920
You think I can't beat you?

13
00:02:16,920 --> 00:02:19,960
- There are only four. How do we do?
- Let's see who's fastest!

14
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:22,520
Grab it! There are four.

15
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:25,960
- Over here.
- Thanks, dude. I'll give you half.

16
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:28,080
- Here comes another! Here we go!
- This has to be...

17
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:31,272
I'm serving, so I'll grab one as well.

18
00:02:33,879 --> 00:02:35,839
Thank you.

19
00:02:36,839 --> 00:02:39,297
Fang Fang. Have one.

20
00:02:39,297 --> 00:02:41,535
Okay, nice.

21
00:02:41,535 --> 00:02:43,480
- Slow down.
- Braised pork shank!

22
00:02:43,480 --> 00:02:44,920
Come on, make some room.

23
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:47,200
Give it to me. Give me.

24
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:49,960
I... I haven't eaten yet.

25
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:52,360
Wait, she hasn't eaten yet.

26
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:55,760
- Here, Grandma. Abalone.
- I didn't do anything.

27
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:57,839
This one.

28
00:02:57,839 --> 00:02:59,526
Look at this pig's head.

29
00:02:59,526 --> 00:03:02,600
Here. Put it here.

30
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:04,320
Enough, okay?

31
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:06,240
Someone hasn't finished yet.

32
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,559
Why are you in such a hurry
to pack it for home?

33
00:03:08,559 --> 00:03:10,040
Are you talking about me?

34
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:12,320
You're the one talking?

35
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:14,839
You paid for one,

36
00:03:14,839 --> 00:03:16,440
but you brought four to eat.

37
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:18,240
Oh, please, Li Lan Fang.

38
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:21,960
You're getting much better value
than I am, right?

39
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:24,479
I didn't see you working this afternoon,

40
00:03:24,479 --> 00:03:27,280
- but you're sure eager to eat.
- Who are you talking about? Me?

41
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:29,720
Didn't I wash all these plates?
Did you see that?

42
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:32,169
Fine. Just keep washing
and don't leave until we're finished.

43
00:03:32,169 --> 00:03:34,600
- Thank you so much.
- Don't say that.

44
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:37,319
Come on, Zhao. Congratulations!

45
00:03:37,319 --> 00:03:39,480
Here comes the fish!

46
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:40,880
Zhao,

47
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:42,799
now that your son is married,

48
00:03:42,799 --> 00:03:45,039
your mission is accomplished.

49
00:03:45,039 --> 00:03:47,127
You can take it easy from now on.

50
00:03:47,127 --> 00:03:49,319
How can I?

51
00:03:49,319 --> 00:03:52,960
Once he's married,
we have to worry about the house.

52
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:55,319
After the house, our grandson will be next.

53
00:03:55,319 --> 00:03:59,757
As parents, when will we ever get a break?

54
00:04:00,599 --> 00:04:01,799
Well,

55
00:04:01,799 --> 00:04:04,800
at least you're halfway
through your Long March.

56
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:09,000
Look at us.
Our two boys are still in high school.

57
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:12,640
We still have a long way to go!

58
00:04:13,745 --> 00:04:15,200
Hao Cheng Gong!

59
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:17,399
Come and toast your Uncle Zhao!

60
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:20,040
Hao Cheng Gong? Who's Hao Cheng Gong?

61
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,630
Fuzz!

62
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:23,086
I'm calling you!

63
00:04:23,086 --> 00:04:24,800
- What are you doing?
- Coming, Dad!

64
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:26,720
Come and toast your Uncle Zhao.

65
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,541
- Hurry up!
- I told you not to call me by my full name.

66
00:04:28,541 --> 00:04:30,440
Come on, I'm telling you, bottom's up.

67
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:32,719
Good boy. Eat up.

68
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:35,486
Fan Tong!

69
00:04:36,159 --> 00:04:37,560
- Is he...
- That's me.

70
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,680
Easy, easy.

71
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:43,120
Dad. My name isn't Fan Tong. It's Fan Tong.

72
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,917
Uncle Zhao.

73
00:04:44,917 --> 00:04:46,605
Good boy. Drink up.

74
00:04:46,605 --> 00:04:50,639
- Happy wedding, brother. Wish you blessings.
- Why did you hit me?

75
00:04:50,639 --> 00:04:52,440
What kind of father are you?

76
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:53,680
How can you call your son that?

77
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:58,079
In the beginning,
I wanted to name him Fan Tong (Unify),

78
00:04:58,079 --> 00:05:00,600
Unifying the world! Does that sound powerful?

79
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:03,440
That word sounds just like glutton.

80
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:04,839
You're the glutton!

81
00:05:04,839 --> 00:05:06,959
Back then, I changed it to this word,

82
00:05:06,959 --> 00:05:09,972
hoping he would gain
a comprehensive knowledge of

83
00:05:09,972 --> 00:05:12,249
both ancient and modern times,
spanning every field.

84
00:05:12,249 --> 00:05:13,880
Everything will be smooth!

85
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:16,720
Good! That's a nice name! Nice name!

86
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,240
- Exactly.
- I mean...

87
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:21,720
I just hope he can have his fill.

88
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:24,519
Look, our old days were so hard.

89
00:05:24,519 --> 00:05:26,440
We couldn't even fill our bellies.

90
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:29,160
Just eat your food. Eat up.

91
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:31,919
Son. Take it.

92
00:05:31,919 --> 00:05:33,240
What's this, Mom?

93
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,327
Treasure!

94
00:05:34,327 --> 00:05:38,199
Your Uncle Pocky dug this out for me.

95
00:05:38,199 --> 00:05:44,045
His son used this secret manual
to get into a top university.

96
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:46,600
Go home and study.

97
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:50,240
If you have questions, ask your brother.

98
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:52,480
- Thank you, Uncle Zhao.
- You've had enough.

99
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:54,280
- Go back and practice.
- Okay.

100
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:56,120
And also, take that...

101
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:59,720
- medicine for your stutter, okay?
- I know, Mom.

102
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:01,964
Good boy, good boy.

103
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:04,643
Eat well.

104
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:14,017
Your name is Fan Tong.

105
00:06:14,017 --> 00:06:15,839
You are Hao Cheng Gong.

106
00:06:15,839 --> 00:06:18,292
Doesn't fit, right?

107
00:06:18,292 --> 00:06:20,440
I've noticed that...

108
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:22,320
you people in Zhazhating are quite interesting.

109
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:25,840
You all look like you're up to no good

110
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:27,560
and shouldn't be messed with,

111
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:31,440
but your names are so full of righteousness.

112
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:34,279
Your name is quite rare too.

113
00:06:34,279 --> 00:06:36,839
What were your parents thinking by then?

114
00:06:36,839 --> 00:06:40,114
Clear skies all over, and kind words always.

115
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:42,240
Do you two get it?

116
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:44,000
No, not at all.

117
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,030
What does it mean?

118
00:06:46,030 --> 00:06:48,032
It means that...

119
00:06:48,759 --> 00:06:51,840
with clear skies

120
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:53,832
and an open mind,

121
00:06:53,832 --> 00:06:55,280
everything you say and do

122
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:57,800
becomes positive.

123
00:06:57,800 --> 00:07:00,639
And they will become a better person.

124
00:07:00,639 --> 00:07:03,079
This is the name my mom gave me.

125
00:07:03,079 --> 00:07:04,759
As a kid, she said:

126
00:07:04,759 --> 00:07:07,199
"Take the right path

127
00:07:07,199 --> 00:07:09,199
to be who you want.

128
00:07:09,199 --> 00:07:12,120
Only then can you reach your goal."

129
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,719
That's how it is! Good name.

130
00:07:13,719 --> 00:07:14,719
Come on.

131
00:07:14,719 --> 00:07:17,920
Here's to clear skies, and what was the rest?

132
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,440
- Kind words always.
- Kind words always! Come on!

133
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:20,802
Come on, drink up!

134
00:07:20,802 --> 00:07:22,320
Wu Lao Er.

135
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:24,719
Are you even a man?

136
00:07:24,719 --> 00:07:26,800
You're from the same neighborhood,

137
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,640
but look at Xing Wu.

138
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:31,073
Why is he always better than you?

139
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:34,617
Fine.

140
00:07:34,617 --> 00:07:37,279
I don't expect you to be able to beat him.

141
00:07:37,279 --> 00:07:41,330
But you can handle that girl beside him, right?

142
00:07:49,073 --> 00:07:51,400
Only cowards chicken out.

143
00:07:58,719 --> 00:08:02,042
- Go drop a little blessing?
- Let's go.

144
00:08:02,042 --> 00:08:05,240
Pocky!

145
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:08,079
- Thank you, thank you.
- Congratulations!

146
00:08:08,079 --> 00:08:09,519
Thank you.

147
00:08:09,519 --> 00:08:11,120
- Come on, let's drink together.
- Thank you for coming today.

148
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,600
That's so nice of you.

149
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,240
I'll drink this. It's liquor.

150
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:16,360
- Okay.
- Slow down.

151
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:18,285
Drink slowly.

152
00:08:18,285 --> 00:08:19,519
- Congratulations!
- Thank you, thank you.

153
00:08:19,519 --> 00:08:20,959
- Congratulations.
- Go easy on yourself.

154
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:22,839
You too.

155
00:08:22,839 --> 00:08:25,371
- Where's the pork shoulder?
- Where's them?

156
00:08:25,371 --> 00:08:27,199
I haven't had any yet!

157
00:08:27,199 --> 00:08:29,717
♪Two little bees, flying among the flowers♪

158
00:08:29,717 --> 00:08:31,040
♪Fly to the left, fly to the right♪

159
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,716
♪Fly♪

160
00:08:32,716 --> 00:08:33,717
♪Fly♪

161
00:08:33,717 --> 00:08:35,240
You're a bug!

162
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:38,440
- Drink up!
- Alright, I'll drink.

163
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:41,320
Grandma, are you finished eating?

164
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:44,200
Yes. Thank you.

165
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,720
I brought some pork shoulder for you.

166
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:50,797
Thank you. That's very thoughtful of you.

167
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:54,080
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

168
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:56,000
Then you must see her home.

169
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,280
- Don't worry, I've got her.
- I'll take Grandma back first.

170
00:08:58,280 --> 00:08:59,921
Okay. Grandma, take it easy.

171
00:08:59,921 --> 00:09:01,320
Be careful on your way back.

172
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:03,159
- Again, one more!
- Okay.

173
00:09:03,159 --> 00:09:05,399
- Our place is quite close.
- Ready, go!

174
00:09:05,399 --> 00:09:08,067
♪Two little bees, flying among the flowers♪

175
00:09:08,067 --> 00:09:09,354
♪Fly to the left, fly to the right♪

176
00:09:09,354 --> 00:09:10,860
♪Fly♪

177
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:12,446
♪Fly♪

178
00:09:12,446 --> 00:09:13,600
Drink!

179
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:16,180
Fine, I'll drink.

180
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:22,880
♪Two little bees, flying among the flowers♪

181
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:24,360
♪Fly to the left, fly to the right♪

182
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:26,520
♪Fly♪

183
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:57,600
♪I want nobody, nobody but you♪

184
00:09:57,600 --> 00:10:03,192
♪I want nobody, nobody but you♪

185
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:14,679
Cross-eyed? Can you do it?

186
00:10:16,159 --> 00:10:17,960
No.

187
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:22,150
I knew you couldn't. Useless.

188
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:30,310
Can you wiggle your ears? Look at me.

189
00:10:31,760 --> 00:10:33,480
- Impressive, right?
- Impressive.

190
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:36,455
You can't? Useless.

191
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:38,919
Can you at least do a backflip?

192
00:10:38,919 --> 00:10:40,000
Come on, show me one.

193
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,092
You're on.

194
00:10:42,092 --> 00:10:44,399
Go!

195
00:10:44,399 --> 00:10:47,759
Impressive, right? You're useless!

196
00:10:47,759 --> 00:10:50,759
Honestly, what are you good at?

197
00:10:50,759 --> 00:10:55,833
Everything you say is just so sharp.

198
00:10:56,759 --> 00:10:59,279
Actually, I can think of one.

199
00:10:59,279 --> 00:11:00,799
And that is...

200
00:11:00,799 --> 00:11:02,960
you get things done.

201
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:06,960
You were the one who found my computer, right?

202
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,799
Nice job!

203
00:11:08,799 --> 00:11:10,799
What, doing good deeds anonymously?

204
00:11:10,799 --> 00:11:12,399
A living saint?

205
00:11:12,399 --> 00:11:13,880
Don't overthink it.

206
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:15,480
I just do what I'm paid for.

207
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:16,919
Since I took your money,

208
00:11:16,919 --> 00:11:20,000
I have to protect your personal and property.

209
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:23,880
Fine. I'll let you complete your good deed.

210
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:26,320
I'm cold.

211
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:42,320
Still cold now?

212
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:44,881
I can't walk.

213
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:48,105
It's only 20 meters away.

214
00:11:48,105 --> 00:11:50,120
You said it yourself.

215
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:52,792
You're doing what you're paid for.

216
00:12:00,919 --> 00:12:03,242
Mount up.

217
00:12:08,655 --> 00:12:10,039
Don't worry.

218
00:12:10,039 --> 00:12:12,480
Even after I leave Zhazhating,

219
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:15,280
I won't forget you.

220
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:18,360
If it's meant to see each other again,

221
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:21,455
let's be friends.

222
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:34,240
What are you doing?

223
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,439
Where's the money?

224
00:12:35,439 --> 00:12:36,600
- Don't go gambling!
- Get away!

225
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,958
- Stop gambling, Xing Guo Dong!
- I'm in a good mood today.

226
00:12:38,958 --> 00:12:40,439
Don't make me hit you!

227
00:12:40,439 --> 00:12:43,630
Xing Guo Dong, come back!

228
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:52,492
[Xing Guo Dong! Pay up your debts!]

229
00:12:52,492 --> 00:12:55,717
[Pay up your debts!]

230
00:13:16,956 --> 00:13:18,600
Grandma! Grandma!

231
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:20,679
Here, don't be afraid.

232
00:13:20,679 --> 00:13:22,320
Alright.

233
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:26,920
There, there. Don't be afraid.

234
00:13:26,920 --> 00:13:29,702
Grandma, I'm here.

235
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:33,080
It's okay, it's okay.

236
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,617
It's all right, Grandma.

237
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:40,567
It's okay.

238
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,800
Don't be scared, Grandma.

239
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:51,735
Grandma, here, take your medicine.

240
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:55,705
Take it easy.

241
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:03,862
There you go. It's all right now.

242
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,559
There's no chance.

243
00:14:16,559 --> 00:14:19,905
You and I are not from the same world.

244
00:14:27,659 --> 00:14:29,399
Wake up.

245
00:14:29,399 --> 00:14:31,742
We're home.

246
00:17:17,439 --> 00:17:20,805
Carbon fiber composite.

247
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:24,161
Titanium alloy.

248
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:27,800
Wu. The design blueprints
and materials are all here.

249
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:30,455
See if anything is missing.

250
00:17:35,959 --> 00:17:37,479
Why are you sighing?

251
00:17:37,479 --> 00:17:40,040
Just say what's on your mind.

252
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:43,800
All that effort, why not build your own?

253
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:46,979
The honor and rewards would be yours.

254
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:53,720
They want the prestige. I want the profit.

255
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:56,509
It's mutually beneficial. A win-win.

256
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:00,080
I just think it's a pity.

257
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:01,479
What's there to be pity about?

258
00:18:01,479 --> 00:18:04,280
With this,
I can get Grandma an electric wheelchair.

259
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:06,155
That's what matters.

260
00:18:06,155 --> 00:18:07,919
I can barely make ends meet.

261
00:18:07,919 --> 00:18:10,159
What use is that empty honor to me?

262
00:18:10,159 --> 00:18:12,089
I don't care.

263
00:18:12,089 --> 00:18:13,520
I understand.

264
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:15,806
But Wu, I just want to know,

265
00:18:15,806 --> 00:18:18,200
is there anyone
or anything else

266
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:21,053
that makes you want to fight for it?

267
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:29,555
Can you do it? Cross-eyed?

268
00:18:29,555 --> 00:18:31,867
Can you wiggle your ears?

269
00:18:31,867 --> 00:18:35,120
Can you at least do a backflip?

270
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:37,572
Even after I leave Zhazhating,

271
00:18:37,572 --> 00:18:40,440
I won't forget you.

272
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:43,536
If it's meant to see each other again,

273
00:18:43,536 --> 00:18:46,148
let's be friends.

274
00:19:05,025 --> 00:19:06,896
Xing Wu.

275
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:10,667
Xing Wu, are you there?

276
00:19:11,520 --> 00:19:13,428
Xing Wu?

277
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:41,399
Honey water helps with hangovers.

278
00:19:41,399 --> 00:19:43,280
I'm at Shunyi. Call me if anything.

279
00:19:43,280 --> 00:19:45,392
Cut back then.

280
00:19:45,392 --> 00:19:47,719
Annoying!

281
00:19:47,719 --> 00:19:51,217
Can't talk nicely, then zip it.

282
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:07,560
Who is it?

283
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:10,040
Someone's in here!

284
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:21,448
If you don't leave, I'll call for help!

285
00:22:34,305 --> 00:22:35,839
[Li Lan Fang]

286
00:22:43,840 --> 00:22:47,180
- 3-bamboo tile.
- 3-bamboo tile? I'll take it.

287
00:22:47,180 --> 00:22:48,520
It smells so good.

288
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:50,600
Green Dragon.

289
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:56,930
Sorry, the subscriber you dialed
is temporarily unavailable.

290
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:22,999
- Hello?
- Hello?

291
00:23:22,999 --> 00:23:26,854
Hello, Xing Wu? I'm in the shower.
Someone is pounding on the door.

292
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:32,000
Qing Ye.

293
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,760
Put your clothes on.
See if there's anything nearby you can use.

294
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:36,886
Keep it in your hand. Don't be afraid.
I'll be right there.

295
00:23:36,886 --> 00:23:38,360
Okay.

296
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:41,842
Call Officer Xu.
Tell him to come to Xuan Island.

297
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:52,346
Hello, Officer Xu.

298
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,402
Qing Ye, it's me.

299
00:25:02,560 --> 00:25:04,740
Come on, get up.

300
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:08,795
Stay here. Don't move.

301
00:25:17,639 --> 00:25:19,999
I told you before. Don't you dare touch her!

302
00:25:19,999 --> 00:25:22,630
I was wrong, I'm sorry.

303
00:25:23,679 --> 00:25:26,280
What are you doing? What's happening?

304
00:25:26,280 --> 00:25:29,542
- Winning hand!
- Not bad!

305
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:38,142
- One more round!
- It's your treat today.

306
00:25:40,439 --> 00:25:41,880
Xing Wu!

307
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:44,840
Stop it! Stop it, Xing Wu!

308
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:47,199
You're so lucky today.

309
00:25:47,199 --> 00:25:49,639
Why do I feel like someone is calling for Wu?
Did you hear that?

310
00:25:49,639 --> 00:25:50,840
No.

311
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:53,399
It's pouring. What can you hear?

312
00:25:53,399 --> 00:25:55,280
Hurry up. Come on, 1-dot tile. My turn.

313
00:25:55,280 --> 00:25:57,687
Stop it.

314
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:32,959
Xing Wu. What's going on?

315
00:26:32,959 --> 00:26:34,719
Wu Lao Er.

316
00:26:34,719 --> 00:26:36,120
Are you okay?

317
00:26:36,120 --> 00:26:38,380
Wu Lao Er.

318
00:26:40,760 --> 00:26:41,800
Fang Fang.

319
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,840
What's going on?
The police are parked at your door.

320
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:45,399
[Xuan Island Barbershop]
Yeah. Why is it parked at our door?

321
00:26:45,399 --> 00:26:48,320
- What's happening?
- This is Officer Xu's car.

322
00:26:48,320 --> 00:26:51,159
What's the matter? So many people here.

323
00:26:51,159 --> 00:26:53,600
- It's Wu Lao Er.
- Lao Er.

324
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:55,755
Isn't this Lao Er?

325
00:26:55,755 --> 00:26:57,520
Son!

326
00:26:57,520 --> 00:26:59,640
- Who beat you up, Lao Er?
- What's going on here?

327
00:26:59,640 --> 00:27:03,360
- Lao Er, what's wrong?
- Lao Er. Who hit you?

328
00:27:04,479 --> 00:27:07,080
What's going on?

329
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:08,320
Who did this?

330
00:27:08,320 --> 00:27:11,087
Did you hit him?

331
00:27:11,087 --> 00:27:13,560
Xing Wu. Did you hit him?

332
00:27:13,560 --> 00:27:15,919
Did you hit him? Was it you?
Did you hit him?

333
00:27:15,919 --> 00:27:17,239
What's wrong with you?

334
00:27:17,239 --> 00:27:19,918
What's going on? Why are you yelling?

335
00:27:19,918 --> 00:27:24,503
- Why did you push my son?
- Look how he beat my son up.

336
00:27:25,639 --> 00:27:27,920
Did you really see my son hit your son?

337
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:28,999
Who hit him? Who?

338
00:27:28,999 --> 00:27:30,840
Alright, alright. Stop shouting.

339
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:31,959
What exactly happened?

340
00:27:31,959 --> 00:27:37,959
Officer, bring us justice please.
Look at how he beat up my son.

341
00:27:37,959 --> 00:27:39,959
I was taking a shower just now.

342
00:27:39,959 --> 00:27:43,040
He kept banging on the door from outside
and trying to break in.

343
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:46,600
If Xing Wu hadn't come back in time...

344
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:49,120
Did you hear that?

345
00:27:49,120 --> 00:27:51,040
What a pervert! Peeping at a girl bathing!

346
00:27:51,040 --> 00:27:52,840
Shameless! My goodness!

347
00:27:52,840 --> 00:27:54,679
What kind of person does that?

348
00:27:54,679 --> 00:27:56,399
- Pervert!
- Exactly. Peeping at a girl...

349
00:27:56,399 --> 00:27:58,280
Who's a creep? Do you have proof?

350
00:27:58,280 --> 00:28:02,496
- Peeping and breaking in!
- You want proof, right?

351
00:28:04,520 --> 00:28:06,280
It's inside Wu Lao Er's house.

352
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:07,399
What do you mean?

353
00:28:07,399 --> 00:28:09,959
Alright. Xiao Liu. Go inside and check.

354
00:28:09,959 --> 00:28:11,999
- Yes, sir.
- Why are you going into our house?

355
00:28:11,999 --> 00:28:14,360
To look for evidence, you know?

356
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:16,999
Wu Lao Er, you're always up to no good.

357
00:28:16,999 --> 00:28:19,159
You still haven't changed at all!

358
00:28:19,159 --> 00:28:20,479
Let me tell you,

359
00:28:20,479 --> 00:28:23,280
if anything happens to Ye,
I won't let your son off!

360
00:28:23,280 --> 00:28:25,880
Officer Xu, look.

361
00:28:28,239 --> 00:28:30,905
Wu Lao Er. Look at this.
Where did this come from?

362
00:28:30,905 --> 00:28:32,760
My goodness.

363
00:28:32,760 --> 00:28:34,840
What if there's a mistake?

364
00:28:34,840 --> 00:28:36,520
- How could there be a mistake?
- Why couldn't there be?

365
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:38,239
It was taken from your house.

366
00:28:38,239 --> 00:28:40,760
- What a pervert.
- Shameless! Pervert!

367
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:44,399
A grown man, keeping a collection
of girls' underwear. Isn't this a bit...

368
00:28:44,399 --> 00:28:45,919
- Alright, alright.
- This is just bullying!

369
00:28:45,919 --> 00:28:49,742
Stop it! Come with me to the station! Let's go.

370
00:28:50,320 --> 00:28:52,600
Thank god.

371
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:54,919
Officer Xu, here is the evidence.

372
00:28:54,919 --> 00:28:56,545
Alright.

373
00:28:57,399 --> 00:29:00,106
Take a look. Is this yours?

374
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:08,680
Yes... it's mine.

375
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:10,310
Wu Lao Er, what's your excuse?

376
00:29:10,310 --> 00:29:12,159
I... I was drunk.

377
00:29:12,159 --> 00:29:16,439
I mistook the toilet for the bathroom.
I didn't mean anything.

378
00:29:16,439 --> 00:29:17,520
Exactly!

379
00:29:17,520 --> 00:29:21,399
It's only because our son was drunk.
So he went into the wrong room.

380
00:29:21,399 --> 00:29:26,080
How could he beat him up like this!
Officer, you've got to help us out!

381
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:28,080
He beat him up so badly!

382
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:30,120
What's with all the pointing?

383
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:32,912
- Look at his face.
- The evidence is all here.

384
00:29:32,912 --> 00:29:34,028
This is useless.

385
00:29:34,028 --> 00:29:35,639
Alright, alright. Stop it.

386
00:29:35,639 --> 00:29:36,719
Take him away.

387
00:29:36,719 --> 00:29:39,399
Where are you taking him?

388
00:29:39,399 --> 00:29:41,760
- I didn't do it! I just went the wrong room.
- Where are you taking him?

389
00:29:41,760 --> 00:29:44,000
Wait a minute.

390
00:29:45,919 --> 00:29:49,012
Did you also steal my computer?

391
00:29:50,399 --> 00:29:51,840
I lost my computer a few days ago.

392
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:53,919
When I checked the surveillance
with Officer Xu,

393
00:29:53,919 --> 00:29:57,199
the thief was wearing these exact clothes.

394
00:29:58,199 --> 00:30:01,159
The police still have my case report
and the CCTV footage.

395
00:30:01,159 --> 00:30:02,800
There is a law.

396
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:06,439
Theft of public or private property valued
between 1,000 and 3,000 yuan or more

397
00:30:06,439 --> 00:30:08,639
is considered a large amount.

398
00:30:08,639 --> 00:30:10,919
Punishable by up to three years in prison.

399
00:30:10,919 --> 00:30:12,880
My computer is worth 15,000 yuan.

400
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,200
What are you talking about?

401
00:30:14,200 --> 00:30:17,520
- It wasn't me. It wasn't me!
- Not you? Stop lying.

402
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:19,959
Do you have to see the CCTV footage?

403
00:30:19,959 --> 00:30:22,600
Go ahead. It wasn't me. I really didn't do it.

404
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:25,680
Wu Lao Er, you're really something.
Look at the footage!

405
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:27,560
Isn't this you? Take him away.

406
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:28,800
- Mom!
- Wait!

407
00:30:28,800 --> 00:30:30,320
- Mom!
- Wait!

408
00:30:30,320 --> 00:30:32,517
What's going on?

409
00:30:32,517 --> 00:30:34,120
Miss.

410
00:30:34,120 --> 00:30:36,840
Miss, please.

411
00:30:36,840 --> 00:30:39,239
Can we just settle this? Okay?

412
00:30:39,239 --> 00:30:43,520
- We worked so hard to raise him.
- That's right.

413
00:30:43,520 --> 00:30:46,952
Please, have mercy. He didn't do it on purpose.

414
00:30:46,952 --> 00:30:48,800
- That's enough.
- I'm begging you.

415
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:50,999
You should've thought of this before.

416
00:30:50,999 --> 00:30:54,177
Look at his poor face.

417
00:30:54,177 --> 00:30:55,560
They don't deserve pity.

418
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:57,942
- Mom!
- Lao Er!

419
00:30:58,840 --> 00:31:00,040
Mom!

420
00:31:00,040 --> 00:31:01,080
Lao Er!

421
00:31:01,080 --> 00:31:02,679
Just you wait!

422
00:31:02,679 --> 00:31:04,840
All of you! You hit my boy!

423
00:31:04,840 --> 00:31:06,280
Why aren't you arresting them?

424
00:31:06,280 --> 00:31:09,867
Lao Er! Lao Er!

425
00:31:13,639 --> 00:31:16,479
Officer Xu. Thank you today.

426
00:31:16,479 --> 00:31:18,120
We brought you trouble again.

427
00:31:18,120 --> 00:31:21,239
It's my duty. No trouble at all.

428
00:31:21,239 --> 00:31:23,560
Wu Lao Er is a repeat offender.

429
00:31:23,560 --> 00:31:24,639
He's incorrigible.

430
00:31:24,639 --> 00:31:27,320
He usually sticks to petty theft.
Nothing we could do.

431
00:31:27,320 --> 00:31:28,880
But this time,

432
00:31:28,880 --> 00:31:30,639
with both witnesses and evidence,

433
00:31:30,639 --> 00:31:32,679
he might go to jail for a while.

434
00:31:32,679 --> 00:31:36,600
Yeah. He deserves.

435
00:31:36,600 --> 00:31:38,999
It's a pity his parents
are still protecting him.

436
00:31:38,999 --> 00:31:40,239
Xing Wu,

437
00:31:40,239 --> 00:31:41,959
come over here.

438
00:31:41,959 --> 00:31:44,115
Officer Xu,

439
00:31:44,115 --> 00:31:45,880
is there anything else we can do?

440
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:49,105
We'll do our best.

441
00:31:50,159 --> 00:31:51,639
Xing Wu,

442
00:31:51,639 --> 00:31:53,959
even though you were doing a good deed,

443
00:31:53,959 --> 00:31:56,080
we don't encourage it.

444
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:58,040
Be careful next time.

445
00:31:58,040 --> 00:32:02,639
Right, I know. Kids these days.
He just doesn't know the line.

446
00:32:02,639 --> 00:32:05,560
It won't happen again. Right, Wu?

447
00:32:05,560 --> 00:32:07,159
Yes. I understand.

448
00:32:07,159 --> 00:32:10,605
Well, then give Officer Xu your word.

449
00:32:10,605 --> 00:32:12,280
Give him your word.

450
00:32:12,280 --> 00:32:13,840
It won't happen again.

451
00:32:13,840 --> 00:32:15,239
I promise.

452
00:32:15,239 --> 00:32:16,280
Alright.

453
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:17,800
You guys should head back.

454
00:32:17,800 --> 00:32:20,679
Okay. We'll head back and get some sleep.

455
00:32:20,679 --> 00:32:22,767
Let's go.

456
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:36,905
Is Ye back?

457
00:32:36,905 --> 00:32:38,800
Hey, Mom, we're back.

458
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:40,919
Grandma.

459
00:32:40,919 --> 00:32:42,320
Are you okay?

460
00:32:42,320 --> 00:32:44,679
She's fine, don't worry.

461
00:32:44,679 --> 00:32:46,959
I'll go check on Wu.

462
00:32:47,959 --> 00:32:50,280
Ye, come.

463
00:32:50,280 --> 00:32:52,239
Come here.

464
00:32:52,239 --> 00:32:54,600
Let me check.

465
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:56,494
Grandma.

466
00:32:58,600 --> 00:33:00,745
You must have been terrified.

467
00:33:01,760 --> 00:33:03,597
I'm okay.

468
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:07,520
There, there.

469
00:33:08,959 --> 00:33:12,867
Let me give you a shoulder.

470
00:33:14,199 --> 00:33:16,320
You're back.

471
00:33:16,320 --> 00:33:19,120
You're back.

472
00:33:19,120 --> 00:33:22,959
Ye, come home.

473
00:33:22,959 --> 00:33:25,679
Ye, don't be afraid.

474
00:33:25,679 --> 00:33:28,730
Ye, come home.

475
00:33:28,730 --> 00:33:32,679
Is Ye back?

476
00:33:32,679 --> 00:33:34,840
I'm back.

477
00:33:35,840 --> 00:33:39,400
That's nice then.

478
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:42,942
My mom used to call me Ye.

479
00:33:43,600 --> 00:33:46,800
Don't be afraid.

480
00:33:46,800 --> 00:33:51,782
Wu is here. No one will bully you.

481
00:33:59,142 --> 00:34:01,092
Don't cry.

482
00:34:01,092 --> 00:34:03,617
Don't cry.

483
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:39,320
Drink some ginger soup.

484
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:41,236
Warm up.

485
00:34:46,592 --> 00:34:48,160
You were in the rain.

486
00:34:48,160 --> 00:34:49,784
Don't get sick.

487
00:34:50,560 --> 00:34:52,908
Drink it now.

488
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:40,521
I miss my mom.

489
00:35:47,399 --> 00:35:49,399
About today...

490
00:35:50,399 --> 00:35:53,567
It won't happen again.

491
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:59,509
- How can you be so sure about that?
- Trust me.

492
00:36:10,399 --> 00:36:12,175
Okay.

493
00:36:13,720 --> 00:36:15,730
I trust you.

494
00:36:24,160 --> 00:36:26,154
For as long as I can remember,

495
00:36:26,154 --> 00:36:28,640
Li Lan Fang loved going to the market,

496
00:36:28,640 --> 00:36:30,559
and brought the fish.

497
00:36:30,559 --> 00:36:34,160
She'd even use a plastic bottle as a fish tank.

498
00:36:34,160 --> 00:36:37,280
The fish would die for no reason.

499
00:36:37,280 --> 00:36:39,160
We were so upset.

500
00:36:39,160 --> 00:36:40,559
She cared for the money,

501
00:36:40,559 --> 00:36:42,919
and I cared for the fish.

502
00:36:43,919 --> 00:36:46,967
Why are you telling me this?

503
00:36:48,240 --> 00:36:49,945
It's like...

504
00:36:50,680 --> 00:36:53,399
The common fish are easier to raise.

505
00:36:53,399 --> 00:36:56,280
The expensive ones are delicate.

506
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:59,760
The common fish can survive on anything.

507
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:04,858
But the expensive ones,
the wrong water will cause their death.

508
00:37:05,559 --> 00:37:07,280
You can't raise koi...

509
00:37:07,280 --> 00:37:09,240
in a plastic bottle.

510
00:37:09,240 --> 00:37:12,280
And roses don't bloom in the desert.

511
00:37:13,360 --> 00:37:15,326
I know.

512
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:18,592
You don't belong here.

513
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:34,831
You're right.

514
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:37,864
Anyway,

515
00:37:39,160 --> 00:37:42,195
I'll be leaving soon.

516
00:37:49,680 --> 00:37:52,160
Before you leave Zhazhating,

517
00:37:52,160 --> 00:37:53,985
I promise...

518
00:37:54,680 --> 00:37:56,600
I'll protect you.

519
00:37:56,600 --> 00:37:59,643
No danger will ever touch you again.

520
00:38:07,120 --> 00:38:08,947
Xing Wu.

521
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:13,956
In all my time here in Zhazhating,

522
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:18,869
this is the first time
you've felt like a brother.

523
00:38:22,760 --> 00:38:24,760
I won't be your brother

524
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:26,964
for much longer.

525
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:36,426
Finish it.

526
00:39:03,079 --> 00:39:05,173
Give me the sign.

527
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:10,680
Isn't it...

528
00:39:10,680 --> 00:39:12,840
a bit too flashy?

529
00:39:12,840 --> 00:39:15,687
That's the point.

530
00:39:30,999 --> 00:39:32,399
I promise.

531
00:39:32,399 --> 00:39:35,911
Your clothes won't go missing.

532
00:39:47,280 --> 00:39:50,220
[Qing Ye Only, Do Not Touch]

533
00:39:59,240 --> 00:40:01,280
When I first came to Zhazhating,

534
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:04,440
problems and worries every day.

535
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:06,800
But after that stormy night,

536
00:40:06,800 --> 00:40:09,767
everything changed.

537
00:40:13,780 --> 00:40:15,505
Time to eat, Ta Ta.

538
00:40:16,273 --> 00:40:18,760
Xing Wu's promise was magical.

539
00:40:18,760 --> 00:40:22,600
It made me feel safe in Zhazhating
for the very first time.

540
00:40:22,600 --> 00:40:27,680
It did make my last few days joyful here.

541
00:40:27,680 --> 00:40:30,039
Watermelon!

542
00:40:30,039 --> 00:40:32,505
Sweet watermelon.

543
00:40:32,505 --> 00:40:35,766
Well! You got a mask, huh?

544
00:40:35,766 --> 00:40:38,897
- I did this.
- Good job.

545
00:40:38,897 --> 00:40:41,520
Wait, isn't this Wu's shirt?

546
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:43,360
- Yes.
- Why did you take it apart?

547
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:45,600
- I need it.
- What for?

548
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:47,751
It's a secret.

549
00:40:48,767 --> 00:40:49,919
Stop laughing.

550
00:40:49,919 --> 00:40:52,834
It's falling, Grandma.

551
00:40:53,760 --> 00:40:56,200
Grandma was afraid I'd lose things again,

552
00:40:56,200 --> 00:41:00,778
so she made haute couture covers
for everything I own.

553
00:41:16,919 --> 00:41:18,880
- How do I look?
- Wonderful!

554
00:41:18,880 --> 00:41:20,439
- Looking good?
- Amazing!

555
00:41:20,439 --> 00:41:22,599
- It's amazing!
- Pretty nice, right?

556
00:41:22,599 --> 00:41:27,285
You're prettier than the models on TV!

557
00:41:29,040 --> 00:41:30,954
Grandma.

558
00:41:38,079 --> 00:41:39,160
Wu.

559
00:41:39,160 --> 00:41:40,999
Come in.

560
00:41:40,999 --> 00:41:42,800
Have some water.

561
00:41:43,840 --> 00:41:46,399
Don't rush out.

562
00:41:46,399 --> 00:41:49,760
Look. I knitted this vest for Ye.

563
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:52,687
Does it look good on her?

564
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:00,776
Yes.

565
00:42:02,552 --> 00:42:04,353
I mean the clothes.

566
00:42:05,280 --> 00:42:08,680
Look at this child! Ignore him.

567
00:42:08,680 --> 00:42:10,969
You really are pretty.

568
00:42:12,479 --> 00:42:15,559
Grandma's knitwear feels so safe.

569
00:42:15,559 --> 00:42:19,780
It's just a bit hot to wear in summer.

570
00:42:21,680 --> 00:42:24,240
Li Lan Fang stopped playing mahjong
at Mahjong Club.

571
00:42:24,240 --> 00:42:27,320
She focused on her cooking in Xuan Island.

572
00:42:27,320 --> 00:42:32,640
She said, "Build up something good to win big."

573
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:37,880
A Pure Flush Deluxe Seven Pairs.

574
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:40,480
The day of my departure came

575
00:42:40,480 --> 00:42:43,079
sooner than I expected.

576
00:42:43,079 --> 00:42:46,600
Those days in Zhazhating were unforgettable.

577
00:42:46,600 --> 00:42:47,760
Peaceful.

578
00:42:47,760 --> 00:42:49,520
Beautiful.

579
00:42:49,520 --> 00:42:51,320
Even after many years,

580
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:55,217
they still sparkle in my memories.

581
00:43:04,919 --> 00:43:06,200
Qing Ye! Qing Ye!

582
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:07,399
Check the school's official website.

583
00:43:07,399 --> 00:43:08,519
The start date was set.

584
00:43:08,519 --> 00:43:09,880
So as the class schedule.

585
00:43:09,880 --> 00:43:11,559
I just talked to He Le Ling.

586
00:43:11,559 --> 00:43:13,320
You can stay at her place before you go abroad.

587
00:43:13,320 --> 00:43:14,680
See you in Beijing.

588
00:43:14,680 --> 00:43:16,709
Xing Wu!

589
00:43:23,959 --> 00:43:26,200
Xing Wu. Xing Wu.

590
00:43:26,200 --> 00:43:28,580
I have some good news.

591
00:43:28,580 --> 00:43:30,972
I'm going back to Beijing.
